channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: As leader race looms, John Thune takes Senate map by storm to boost GOP candidates
item.description: South Dakota Sen. John Thune is blitzing battleground states for candidates in competitive races as he vies to be the next Senate Republican leader in November.

item.title: Shigeru Ishiba to lead Japan after dramatic intra-party vote
item.description: Former Defense Minister Shigeru Ishiba on Friday won a race to lead Japan's conservative ruling Liberal Democratic Party, a victory that puts him in line to succeed resigning Prime Minister Fumio Kishida.

item.title: The Real Three Mile Island Disaster Was Shutting It Down
item.description: The unjustly maligned nuclear plant might soon be up and running again as America’s misguided war against nuclear power de-escalates.

item.title: Texas Police Investigating Claim Election Volunteer Tried To Register Minor To Vote
item.description: Multiple agencies are looking into the incident reportedly involving a volunteer attempting to register a minor.

item.title: Vulnerable Dem senator ripped for votes on key 2024 Rust Belt issue: 'Lockstep' with Harris
item.description: Ohio Dem. Sen. Sherrod Brown is facing increased criticism on his fracking stance as the issue becomes more prevalent in the 2024 election.

item.title: Democratic donors fork over thousands to launch right-wing spoiler candidates
item.description: A collection of liberal activists and donors from around the country suddenly decided to send tens of thousands of dollars to right-wing, third-party candidates who could act as spoilers and help Democrats win pivotal races in the battle for control of the House and Senate.

item.title: The Week: The Feds Indict Eric Adams
item.description: Plus: The White Sox lose 120 games.

item.title: Advertising Company Axes Catholic Group’s Pro-Trump Billboard Display
item.description: The Lamar Advertising Company rejected a billboard design from Catholics for Catholics that contained a prayer for Donald Trump.

item.title: North Carolina removes 747,000 from voter rolls
item.description: The North Carolina Board of Elections dropped over 747,000 individuals from state voter rolls via an audit that began at the beginning of 2023, the board announced this week.

item.title: New York City Mayor Eric Adams arrives at court in illegal-contributions case
item.description: New York City's embattled and indicted mayor, Eric Adams, arrived at court Friday morning ahead of an appearance on charges that he accepted illegal campaign contributions and free overseas trips from people looking to buy his influence in city government.

item.title: Communism Yesterday, Today . . . and Tomorrow?
item.description: An interview with historian Sean McMeekin.

item.title: Woke Economists’ Kamala Endorsement Prioritizes Ideology Over Reality
item.description: Despite all existing data exposing Harris as an economic disaster, more than 400 economists are turning to misinformation to hurt Trump.

item.title: Multiple people with ties to Iran indicted in relation to Trump campaign hacking plot: sources
item.description: Multiple people with connections to Iran have been indicted in relation to a hacking plot against former President Donald Trump's campaign Specific charges have also not yet been released.

item.title: Jews and Catholics warn against Trump's latest loyalty test for religious voters
item.description: Former President Donald Trump recently reissued his loyalty test to religious Americans, declaring that he can best protect their freedoms while preemptively blaming members of certain faiths should he lose the presidential election in November.

item.title: The Secret Service Is a National Embarrassment
item.description: This sort of ineptitude wouldn’t be tolerated by Taylor Swift’s security detail.

item.title: Trump Assassination Attempts Are The Logical Result Of The Left’s Marxist ‘Oppression’ Narrative
item.description: Despite a second assassination attempt on former President Donald Trump in two months, Democrats refuse to relinquish their extremist rhetoric. This inciting rhetoric persists because a fixation on violence pervades the left. More than a political strategy, Democrats’ extremist rhetoric is the product of the leftist ideologies that now rule them. President Joe Biden kicked […]

item.title: White House declines to say if Iran killing Trump would be an 'act of war'
item.description: President Biden is resisting Republican demands to warn Iran in no uncertain terms that killing President Trump would be an act of war.

item.title: Harris heads to the U.S.-Mexico border to face down criticism of her record
item.description: Vice President Kamala Harris on Friday will make her first visit to the U.S.-Mexico border since becoming the Democratic presidential nominee to confront head-on one of her biggest vulnerabilities ahead of the November election.

item.title: Will the Real Tim Walz Please Stand Up?
item.description: A trip through Walz’s home state of Minnesota reveals widespread confusion about what Walz believes and who he is.

item.title: If Harris Can ‘Eliminate The Filibuster For Roe,’ She Can Nuke It For Fracking Bans And Gun Control Too
item.description: Democrats will use abortion as a 'wedge' issue to nuke the filibuster, allowing them to enact many other bad policies.
